  "prompt": "What is the salary of vlsi fresher in India?",
  "response": "As of my last update, the salary of a VLSI (Very-Large-Scale Integration) fresher in India varies depending on several factors, such as the location, the company, the candidate's educational background, and the demand for VLSI skills at the time. On average, a VLSI fresher in India might expect a starting salary ranging from INR 3.5 lakh to INR 7 lakh per annum. \n\nTop companies or those located in major tech hubs like Bangalore, Hyderabad, or Pune might offer higher starting salaries, potentially exceeding INR 8 lakh per annum for candidates from prestigious institutions or those with exceptional skills. Keep in mind that these figures are subject to change, and the actual salary may vary based on dynamic industry trends.",
